quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  12,94,"And when the caravan departed, their father said: "
  12,95,"They said: "
  12,96,"Then, when the bearer of the glad tidings arrived, he cast it (the shirt) over his face, and he became clear-sighted. He said: "
  14,40,""
  14,41,""
  14,42,"Consider not that Allâh is unaware of that which the Zâlimûn (polytheists, wrong-doers) do, but He gives them respite up to a Day when the eyes will stare in horror."
  15,13,"They would not believe in it (the Qur’ân); and already the example of (Allâh’s punishment of) the ancients (who disbelieved) has gone forth."
  15,14,"And even if We opened to them a gate from the heaven and they were to keep on ascending thereto (all the day long)"
  15,15,"They would surely say (in the evening): "